    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54B32 3.2L inline-six, equipped with individual throttle bodies and a 7,900 RPM redline. This example utilizes a 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox paired with a factory M-Variable limited-slip differential. To ensure long-term mechanical reliability, the rod bearings have been replaced and the rear subframe has been professionally reinforced to mitigate floor pan fatigue. The VANOS system has been overhauled using Beisan systems components for precise variable valve timing. The chassis features refreshed bushings and Bilstein B6 dampers, maintaining original kinematics with improved rebound control. While the paint exhibits minor stone chips consistent with spirited use, the drivetrain is mechanically synchronized and provides the visceral, analog feedback expected of this platform.",
